Specifying `popup_during_fullscreen smart' also does not work as specified in Section 4.18 of the current documentation.

How do I get the functionality back in the newer version?</description><pubDate>Sat, 08 Feb 2014 18:57:38 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3382/popups-during-fullscreen-mode/</guid></item><item><title>Comment by Michael for &lt;p&gt;In version 3.e, relevant popups would always show when in fullscreen mode. Ever since upgrading from version 3.e to version 4.6, pop ups never show when a window is in fullscreen mode. Instead, I am forced to leave fullscreen mode to see the popup window. This is true for all applications that I have used (e.g. open-file dialogue of inkscape).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Specifying `popup&lt;em&gt;during&lt;/em&gt;fullscreen smart' also does not work as specified in Section 4.18 of the current documentation.&lt;/p&gt;

